Fixed the Rook's movements(changed ifs and loops to four separate cases: up, down, right, or left), changed players after movment so only one can go at a time (starts with white), included a border so that you can see when you've selected a piece, changed isValidMove for ChessPiece to allow for captures, and fixed pawn's movement when capturing
I added a blue border around possible move locations. Reveals some issues that still need to be ironed out. Committing so you can test with it if you want

I got the rook working and added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I got the rook working and added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I added an undo button to the jmenubar (temporarily). I added undo functionality and got it working with regular moves and captures. I added en passant for the pawn (it's a special move in chess) and got it to work with undo.

I got inCheck working and added a method that returns an array of moves that will escape check. I set the actionlistener up so that a player in check must get out of check and the board highlights pieces differently when a piece is in check.

I changed isValidMove to include returning false if a move will put the player in check. I had to change a lot of code layout to get this implemented, so I removed the capturing method and just included it in the move method, and changed the method that made an array of possible moves. I added a method that sorts through the array of possible moves and removes moves that put a player in check. I had to separate these (unfortunately). I also changed the actionlistener so that not being able to put yourself in check would not be prevented there, but only verified.

Changed the gui and added a timer and captures panel. Put the board on its own panel and added it to the class panel in a gridbaglayout. Timer is mostly working but needs polishing. Changed undo to undo board states instead of individual moves.
Made the ChessAI file but needs to be coded

Changed back the code for undo so it undoes moves instead of board states. Also fixed en passant for the pawns so to follow the rules. Changed updating the captures panel so undoing a capture removes a piece from the panel. Finally added scores to the pieces in the AI so we can use that to make the AI make smart moves.
There was a problem where the AI didn't have access to the board

Here are all the files for reading and writing moves. I changed the castling code just a bit because it wasn't working on the queen side, added a statement to check what the newColumn is. AI is commented out and so is playing the moves off the sample game. Changed AI so all methods from ChessModel are referenced through the variable model. I got rid of any methods we weren't using in the AI

Reformatted the gui and added the timer panel back, it isn't causing problems for me and I wanted to cut down on the parameters for the panel class but I understand if we need to move it back. I added a save and load game option and worked out the kinks in resetting the game. Also fixed some functionality for the game file handler and improved my ai system. I added a method to make a random move in case we need it.
TODO: figure out how to add an option to enable or disable the AI TODO: I'd like to add a panel to see the code generated by the move order, but I don't know where to put it or if there's even a good spot for it. TODO: add a dialog for when a person wins. Do we care about stalemate? I don't think so?

added a panel for the move sequence that works with undoing and choosing a new game. Fixed a bug in removing the last move from the sequence where it would remove only part of a move if the row was equal to the turn
